Detailed Description

The class represents a GET_SESSIONS_RESPONSE message. The message structure is as follows: <xmp> struct GetSessionsResponse { struct IPDRStreamingHeader header; short requestId; // allows match up of response to request struct SessionBlock sessionBlocks <>; // description of supported Sessions } </xmp> A session block has the following structure: <xmp> struct SessionBlock { char sessionId; char reserved; UTF8String sessionName; // Optional names and description for the Session UTF8String sessionDescription; int ackTimeInterval; // the maximum time between acks for this Session in sec. int ackSequenceInterval; // the maximum number of unacknowledged data items } </xmp>
